# Force LF line endings for all text files, regardless of the checkout
# platform's core.autocrlf setting. Shell scripts are executed directly by
# bash (via `bash script.sh`, not through a Windows-native interpreter), and
# a stray \r corrupts the last token on any line — e.g. `set -euo pipefail\r`
# fails with "invalid option name" only on Windows checkouts where Git for
# Windows' common core.autocrlf=true default silently converts LF -> CRLF.
* text=auto eol=lf

*.sh text eol=lf
